description.narrative: This activity (Supporting Government Reform in Uzbekistan) is a component of National School of Government International (NSGI) support to country programmes in sustainable centre of government reforms. reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £1,058,015. This component benefits Uzbekistan, and works in the following sector(s): Public sector policy and administrative management. , with the following implementing partners: Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office, Palladium International Ltd (UK). The start date is 17-05-2018 and the end date is 31-05-2021.
